### Adding Resource Templates

To add additional resource types (e.g., a pool for consumables):

```python
from madsci.common.types.resource_types import Pool

consumable_pool = Pool(
    resource_name="{{ module_name }}_consumable",
    resource_class="{{ module_name | pascal_case }}Consumable",
    capacity=100.0,
    attributes={"description": "Consumable resource pool"},
)

self.resource_client.init_template(
    resource=consumable_pool,
    template_name="{{ module_name }}_consumable_pool",
    description="Template for {{ module_name }} consumable pool.",
    required_overrides=["resource_name"],
    tags=["{{ module_name }}", "consumable", "pool"],
    created_by=self.node_definition.node_id,
    version="1.0.0",
)
```

